#Data Preparation 
new_df=pd.merge(cust,order,on='customer_id')
new_df['op_month']=new_df.order_purchase_timestamp.dt.month
new_df['op_year']=new_df.order_purchase_timestamp.dt.year
new_df=new_df[['op_year','op_month','customer_unique_id']].sort_values(by=['op_year','op_month'])
aqc_all=new_df.drop_duplicates(subset=['customer_unique_id'],keep='first',ignore_index=True)

#Data Prepartion
T1=pd.DataFrame(ord_pay.groupby(by='order_id')['payment_value'].sum()).reset_index()
T2=pd.merge(order,T1,on='order_id')
T2.drop_duplicates(subset='order_id',inplace=True)
#T2=T2.loc[T2.order_status!="canceled",['order_purchase_timestamp','payment_value']]
T2.rename(columns={'payment_value':'Sales'},inplace=True)

#Extracting Date parts
T2['Month_name']=T2.order_purchase_timestamp.dt.month_name()
T2['Month_no']=T2.order_purchase_timestamp.dt.month
T2['Weekday_name']=T2.order_purchase_timestamp.dt.day_name()
T2['Weekday']=T2.order_purchase_timestamp.dt.dayofweek
T2['Day_of_month']=T2.order_purchase_timestamp.dt.day
T2['Hour_of_day']=T2.order_purchase_timestamp.dt.hour
T2['Week_of_year']=T2.order_purchase_timestamp.dt.weekofyear
T2['year']=T2.order_purchase_timestamp.dt.year

axis[0,1].set_xlabel(None)

2. Performing Customers/sellers Segmentation¶

a. Divide the customers into groups based on the revenue generated

In [34]:
temp1=pd.DataFrame(pd.merge(ord_pay,order,on='order_id').groupby(by='customer_id').payment_value.sum())
#function for quantile
def grp(y):
    g=np.quantile(temp1.payment_value,y)
    return(g)
temp1['Segment']=pd.cut(temp1.payment_value,[0,grp(0.25),grp(0.5),grp(0.75),grp(1)],
                        labels=['Very Low Revenue','Low Revenue','High Revenue','Very High Revenue'])

Product Category(Groups) Cross Selling : Top 10¶

In [37]:
table2=pd.crosstab(table1.order_id,table1.cat_type)

table2['Cardinality']=table2.sum(axis=1)

                                                                table2.columns.difference(['Cardinality']))
